headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 31 points, Bogdan Bogdanovic made the most of his first start of the season with 28 points on 7-of-10 shooting from 3-point range and the depleted Atlanta Hawks handed the Charlotte Hornets their seventh straight loss, 125-106 on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 31, Hawks hold off Ball, Hornets 125-106

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 23 points and 13 rebounds and the Sacramento Kings used a dominant performance from their starters to beat the Detroit Pistons 122-113 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis, Fox lead Kings to 122-113 victory over Pistons

headlines.description: — Moritz Wagner scored 25 points and Paolo Banchero added 20 as the Orlando Magic beat the NBA-leading Boston Celtics 117-109 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Moritz Wagner powers Magic past NBA-leading Celtics 117-109

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 18 of his 41 points in the fourth quarter and the Cleveland Cavaliers rallied from a 13-point deficit to beat the Indiana Pacers 118-112 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 41, Cavaliers rally to beat Pacers 118-112

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 34 points and 13 rebounds, James Harden added 27 points and nine assists and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the short-handed Golden State Warriors 118-106 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid, Harden lead 76ers past short-handed Warriors

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving hit a game-winning 3-pointer at the buzzer and the Brooklyn Nets rallied to beat the Toronto Raptors 119-116 on Friday night, extending their winning streak to a season-high five.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving hits game-winning 3 at buzzer, Nets win 5th straight

events.name: New York Knicks at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett scored 27 points and the New York Knicks again used 3-point shooting to beat the Chicago Bulls, 114-91 on Friday night to sweep the two-game set and run their winning streak to six.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks launch 3s, beat Bulls 114-91 for 6th straight victory

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Naz Reid loves playing against Oklahoma City.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reid scores 28 as Timberwolves top Thunder, snap 3-game skid

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 33 points, Christian Wood had a season-high 32 points along with 12 rebounds and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Portland Trail Blazers 130-110 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Wood lead Mavericks to 130-110 win over Blazers

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James scored 30 points, Russell Westbrook had 15 points, 12 assists and 11 rebounds and the Los Angeles Lakers smoothly overcame Anthony Davis' latest injury in a 126-108 victory over the Denver Nuggets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis injured, but LeBron leads Lakers past Denver 126-108
